{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/herpes-simplex-ocular/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"e66ffea9-ef64-58b0-a635-c1cdca2add0c","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 08e47967-3e95-4734-8048-a7f2018868f0 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 08e47967-3e95-4734-8048-a7f2018868f0 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 21f20cdf-c253-466a-bc32-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field f33a2768-514c-4958-8194-a7f2018868f0 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field f33a2768-514c-4958-8194-a7f2018868f0 --><!-- begin field e8e6f661-2706-4944-9669-a7f2018868f0 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field e8e6f661-2706-4944-9669-a7f2018868f0 --><!-- begin field bbe54685-1b99-4fea-927b-a7f2018868f0 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field bbe54685-1b99-4fea-927b-a7f2018868f0 --><!-- begin field f1f6c73f-a5b5-4371-9372-a7f2018868f0 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field f1f6c73f-a5b5-4371-9372-a7f2018868f0 --><!-- begin field eaa001f2-c28e-45e8-8bbe-a7f2018868f0 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field eaa001f2-c28e-45e8-8bbe-a7f2018868f0 --><!-- begin field 79ba52f4-85cf-4471-8ce1-a7f2018868f0 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 79ba52f4-85cf-4471-8ce1-a7f2018868f0 --><!-- end item 21f20cdf-c253-466a-bc32-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"be4f3502-607b-5fee-a51f-95c6bd0b5ec2","topicId":"3d44f060-93e8-484f-9435-bbf95181522e","topicName":"Herpes simplex - ocular","slug":"herpes-simplex-ocular","lastRevised":"Last revised in November 2016","chapters":[{"id":"32c3fcc5-456d-5b9d-aef9-f9b7c680badd","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"da713d91-bc3d-5555-b895-94dbfb914de7","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"80008612-da47-5830-afb3-976738b8bf37","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"b8f32462-8266-5dab-84a0-98008de3a98a","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"b5bcc37c-9baa-52ae-a626-8f354255e727","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"19396da1-78c6-52cf-a8fa-745a86678eb2","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"b60fab70-f81b-5b0d-9b5d-08bd0dc46221","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"3eb1fb97-b9d8-5e05-a603-311b22d98080","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"0f62044c-c052-5413-8ef8-21290d58e558","slug":"audit-criteria","f